<item>
            <title>[BOOKKEEPER-114] add a shutdown hook to shut down bookie server safely.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BOOKKEEPER-114</link>
                <project id="12311293" key="BOOKKEEPER">Bookkeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, if Bookie server is terminated, e.g. CTRL-C, kill -SIGTERM pid, kill pid, the data buffered in BufferedChannel has no chanced to be flushed, which may make files corrupted. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should add a shutdown hook to shut down bookie server safely, which will be called when JVM is terminated.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12531924">BOOKKEEPER-114</key>
